    "body": "Are we sure this should be closed? \r\n\r\nAfter following this guide, https://blog.zeppelin.solutions/how-to-create-token-and-initial-coin-offering-contracts-using-truffle-openzeppelin-1b7a5dae99b6\r\n\r\nI set the tokens rate to 1000, my understanding is that should be 1000 tokens per ether, but it is actually per wei. So 1 ether = '1e+21' tokens. Which seems a bit high...\r\n\r\nI can't seem to pass in a decimal, to force division, so I am a little stuck here. It seems that I am stuck at 1 token per wei, which is one billion billion tokens per ether. Not really numbers I feel like dealing with.\r\n\r\nAm i missing something obvious?",
