    "body": "Turns out I'm a durp, but I can explain it for other people I think, who might come here with the same confusion.\r\n\r\nI had decimals set to 18. But the contract isn't using floats, so 18 decimals of precision, is actually 18 extra zeros. So in order to get your token amount in truffle, use:\r\n```js\r\n     web3\r\n        .toBigNumber(tokenCount)\r\n        .div('1e+18') // 18 should be whatever number of decimals you have set.\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
